About me

I develop user interfaces for web applications. I enjoy what I do because I believe technology is a tool that we can use to unlock human potential. I think this is true not just for the users of the technology, but also for the individuals that develop that technology as well.

The more we learn and the more we help each other learn, the better we become as individuals and a community!

I use front end web technologies as well as Node.js + serverless services as the tools for my craft.

Some fun facts about me are that 1) I'm from an island but I don't like seafood 2) My first name means "The One Who Wanders" in Hawaiian and 3) When not coding, you can find me taking care of my family or playing Final Fantasy.

Design choices

With every project I do, I work to strike a balance between using new features such as CSS Grid or async functions while not excluding users who may not be on the latest devices and browsers.

I use tools such as Webpack, Babel, PostCSS, and Browsersync to make sure the features I decide to use work in all the environments I aim to support. This portfolio and all the projects in it are responsive and work in the major browsers such as Firefox, Chrome, Safari and even Internet Explorer 11!

Thanks for viewing and I hope you have a good experience.

Projects

PiChat

Chat with a Raspberry Pi. Subscribe to real-time updates of its temperature readings. Built with GraphQL and React.

Star Wars Guess Who Game

Guess the random character and see how high you can get your streak of correct guesses. Built with React, Node, and AWS services.

Final Fantasy MiniWiki

View quick facts about your favorite Final Fantasy characters with this React / Redux app.

HydraBase

A prototype of an app designed to help fire fighters. Developed at the 2018 AT&T IoT Civic Hackathon and uses the Google Maps API.

Simon - Morph Edition

Exercise your memory muscles with this game of tones, lights, and patterns. Developed with async functions.

Drawn Tic-Tac-Toe

This app draws itself across your screen using SVG animation and invites you to challenge the CPU to this classic game.

Spinning Pomodoro

Work in productive bursts with a little help from the timer that uses SVG animation to show you know how much time you have left.

K-Calc

A 3D calculator from the future for all your computation needs. Built with CSS 3D transforms and animation.

Wikipedia Gateway

A simple interface built on top of the MediaWiki action API to help you find Wikipedia content with search keywords.
